Our Reporter  AFROBEAT diva, Yemi Eberechi Alade, simply known as Yemi Alade has dropped the visual of her hit single titled, ‘Shekere’ featuring Grammy award winner Angélique Kidjo. ‘Shekere’ means Tambourine is the sixth single off Yemi Alade’s fourth studio album “Woman of Steel“. The album features top music artistes include like Rick Ross, Angélique Kidjo, Duncan Mighty and Nollywood star Funke Akindele. In the colourful video, both singers dressed in African attire and neck graced with pieces of jewellery as they imitate their dance steps.  Kidjo who recently won her fourth Grammy speak about  the importance of encouraging the new generation of African artistes. “The new generation of artists coming from Africa is going to take you by storm and the time has come,” she said She gained prominence after winning the Peak Talent Alade who always refers herself as Mama gained prominence after winning the Peak Talent Show in 2009, and is best known for her hit single “Johnny”in 2009, and is best known for her hit single ‘Johnny’.